						               													<description>Fraction Mania is an educational game designed to teach children to represent the fractions 1/2, 1/3, 1/4, 1/5, 1/6 and 1/8.  The game uses a solar system theme with planets associated with each of the six fractions above, as well as comets (represented by marbles and additional cards for use with some of the variants.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The equipment provided can be used to play four variants:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;1) Beginner's Mania -- Each player in turn rolls a die and collects the appropriate piece in a race to fill his/her planets first.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;2) Fraction Mania -- The basic game with the addition of event cards and a requirement for a player to trade up and down to the largest possible fraction he/she can use.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;3) Double Mania -- A player can now collect multiple fraction pieces in a given turn and exchange them for equivalent sets on the fly.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;4) Action Mania -- A timed game using written logs instead of the planets; the players take turns rolling a die and adding the roll to a log, trading up as appropriate.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
